{"title_page": "George Brinkman murders", "text_new": "'''George Brinkman Jr.''' (born 1972) is an American [[murderer]] who took the lives of five people during a 2017 [[killing spree]].<ref name= \"ODRC\"/><ref name= \":1\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.beaconjournal.com/news/20191001/george-brinkman-jr-found-guilty-in-lake-township-slayings|title=George Brinkman Jr. found guilty in Lake Township slayings|first=Ed|last=Balint|date=October 1, 2019|website=beaconjournal.com}}</ref> His first victims were Suzanne Taylor, with whom he had been friends since elementary school, and her two daughters, twenty-one-year-old Taylor Pifer and eighteen-year-old Kylie Pifer. On June 10, 2017, Brinkman took the women [[Captivity|captive]] inside their home in [[North Royalton, Ohio]]. He killed Taylor in front of her daughters before killing them as well.<ref name= \":2\">{{cite press release |date= December 28, 2018|title= George Brinkman Sentenced to Death for the Murders of 45-year-old Suzanne Taylor, and her two daughters, Taylor Pifer, 21, and Kylie Pifer, 18|url=http://prosecutor.cuyahogacounty.us/en-US/2018-12-28-pr-George-Brinkman-Sentenced-to-Death.aspx |agency=Cuyahoga County Office of the Prosecutor}}</ref> Brinkman then went to the [[Lake Township, Ohio]] home of seventy-one-year-old Rogell \u201cGene\u201d John and his sixty-four-year-old wife Roberta \u201cBobbi\u201d John. Brinkman, who had known the couple for over ten years, [[Gunshot wound|shot]] them both to death.<ref name= \":1\"/>\n\nBrinkman [[pleaded guilty]] to the North Royalton murders in November 2018 and to the Lake Township murders in October 2019.<ref name= \":3\"/><ref name= \":4\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.wkyc.com/article/news/crime/man-who-pleaded-guilty-in-north-royalton-slayings-pleads-guilty-to-two-more-in-stark-county/95-9f750169-0260-45bc-9e87-8885dfede17d|title=Man who pleaded guilty in 3 North Royalton slayings, pleads guilty for 2 more in Stark County|date=October 2, 2019|website=wkyc.com}}</ref> He was [[sentenced to death]] for murdering Taylor and her daughters in December 2018.<ref name= \":2\"/> In October 2019 he received another death sentence for murdering the Johns.<ref name= \":5\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.cleveland19.com/2019/10/04/convicted-killer-receive-sentencing-after-admitting-additional-murders/ |title=Convicted killer receives death sentence for murdering Stark County couple|first=Alan|last= Rodges|date=October 4, 2019|website=cleveland19.com}}</ref> Brinkman is currently on [[death row]] at the [[Chillicothe Correctional Institution]] in [[Chillicothe, Ohio]].<ref name= \"ODRC\"/>\n\n==Background==\n===Victims===\nSuzanne Taylor was from [[Parma Heights, Ohio]]. She graduated from [[Valley Forge High School]] in 1990<ref name= \"Heavy\">{{Cite web|url=https://heavy.com/news/2017/06/suzanne-taylor-kylie-pifer-north-royalton-ohio-mother-daughters-murder-photos/|title=Suzanne Taylor, Kylie & Taylor Pifer: 5 Fast Facts You Need to Know|first=Tom|last=Cleary|date=Jun 13, 2017|website=heavy.com}}</ref> and went on to attend [[Hiram College]] where she earned a bachelor of arts degree in [[psychology]], [[sociology]], and [[political science]]. She worked as an administrator at REO Property Consultants, starting in 2012, and as a [[real estate appraiser]] for Forsythe Appraisals, starting in 2013.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.linkedin.com/in/suzanne-taylor-2ab69551|title=Suzanne Taylor|website=linkedin.com}}</ref> Taylor lived in the [[Cleveland]] suburb of North Royalton, Ohio, with her two daughters, Kylie Pifer, eighteen, and Taylor Pifer, twenty-one.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.10tv.com/article/ohio-man-convicted-3-killings-set-trial-2-more-2019-may|title=Ohio man convicted in 3 killings is set for trial in 2 more|date=May 6, 2019|website=10tv.com}}</ref><ref name= \":6\">{{Cite web|url=https://fox8.com/news/man-accused-of-killing-north-royalton-family-to-be-sentenced-friday/|title=Man who killed North Royalton family sentenced to death penalty|first1=Natasha|last1=Anderson| first2=Matt|last2=Wright|date=December 28, 2018|website=fox8.com}}</ref> Taylor Pifer was a 2014 graduate of [[North Royalton High School]] and had just completed her junior year at [[Kent State University]]. She played softball while in high school and worked at the Kent State Fashion Management Store while in college.<ref name= \"Heavy\"/> She was working towards obtaining a bachelors degree in [[fashion design]] and [[merchandising]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.wayup.com/profile/Taylor-Pifer-37688a0b07/|title=Taylor Pifer|website=wayup.com}}</ref> Kylie Pifer was set to begin her sophomore year at [[Bowling Green State University]] in the fall of 2017.  She was involved in theater and studied [[biology]],<ref name= \"Heavy\"/> and aspired to become a [[forensic scientist]].<ref name= \":7\"/> She would have turned nineteen on Sunday, June 18, 2017.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.kentwired.com/latest_updates/article_1777830c-5184-11e7-a732-4fec2ca0ab71.html|title=Community mourns slain student, family at candlelight vigil|first=Elizabeth|last=Harrington|date=June 15, 2017|website=kentwired.com}}</ref>\n\nRogell E. \u201cGene\u201d John II (born 1945) was a graduate of [[East Canton High School]] and Bowling Green State University.<ref name= \":8\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.sandersfuneralhomes.com/obituary/Rogell-John|title=Rogell E. \"Gene\" John|website=sandersfuneralhomes.com}}</ref> He was also a [[Vietnam War veteran]]. Mr. John worked in the circulation department of [[The Canton Repository]] and served as the circulation director at The Massillon Independent and GateHouse Ohio. He then started his own business distributing telephone books and publications.<ref name= \":9\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.indeonline.com/news/20191003/stark-county-judges-hand-george-brinkman-two-more-death-sentences|title=George BrinkmanStark County judges hand George Brinkman two more death sentences|first=Ed|last=Balint|date=October 3, 2019|website=indeonline.com}}</ref><ref name= \":10\"/> He was married to Roberta R. \u201cBobbi\u201d John (born 1952), a [[North Canton Hoover High School]], [[Ohio University]] and [[Akron University]] graduate. Before retirement, Mrs. John worked as the Director of Special Services for [[Stow-Munroe Falls City School District]].<ref name= \"Legacy Bobbi\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.legacy.com/obituaries/cantonrep/obituary.aspx?n=roberta-r-bobbi-john&pid=185844075&fhid=6475|title=Roberta R. Bobbi JOHN|website=legacy.com}}</ref> She also worked for the [[Alliance, Ohio|Alliance]] and [[Louisville, Ohio|Louisville]] school districts.<ref name= \":9\"/> Both Mr. and Mrs. John were active members of  Mt. Tabor United Methodist Church, the Osnaburg Historical Society.<ref name= \"Legacy Bobbi\"/><ref name= \":8\"/> The couple lived in Lake Township, Ohio.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://abc6onyourside.com/news/local/man-argues-for-his-own-death-sentence-in-couples-slaying |title=Man argues for his own death sentence in couple's slaying|date=October 3, 2019|website=abc6onyourside.com}}</ref>\n\n===Perpetrator===\nGeorge Brinkman (born 1972)<ref name= \"ODRC\">{{Cite web|url=https://appgateway.drc.ohio.gov/OffenderSearch/Search/Details/A764906|title=Offender Details}}</ref> knew all of his victims well.<ref name= \":11\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.news5cleveland.com/news/local-news/oh-stark/who-is-george-brinkman-suspect-in-the-lake-township-and-north-royalton-homicides|title=Who is George Brinkman? Suspect in the Lake Township and North Royalton homicides|first1=Megan|last1=Hickey|first2=Courtney |last2=Danser|date=June 13, 2017|website=news5cleveland.com}}</ref> He went to elementary school with Suzanne Taylor and remained friends with her through adulthood.<ref name= \":7\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.cleveland.com/court-justice/2018/12/george-brinkman-jr-sentenced-to-death-in-slayings-of-north-royalton-woman-daughters.html|title=George Brinkman Jr. sentenced to death in slayings of North Royalton woman, daughters|first=Cory|last=Shaffter|date=December 28, 2018 |website=cleveland.com}}</ref> Neighbors of Taylor and the Pifer sisters say that Brinkman often visited their home.<ref name= \":11\"/> Taylor let Brinkman do various jobs around her house and also allowed him to sleep in her house during times when he was [[homeless]].<ref name= \":7\"/> Taylor's family believes that Brinkman wanted to be \u201cmore than friends\u201d with her.<ref name= \":6\"/> According to witnesses, the Pifer women looked up to Brinkman like a \u201csecond father.\u201d<ref name= \":3\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.cleveland.com/court-justice/2018/11/north-royalton-man-admits-killing-woman-daughters-as-judges-hear-evidence-in-potential-death-penalty-case.html|title=North Royalton man admits killing woman, daughters, as judges hear evidence in potential death-penalty case|first=Cory|last=Shaffer|date=November 5, 2018|website=cleveland.com}}</ref>\n\nBrinkman knew the John couple for more than ten years.<ref name= \":12\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.indeonline.com/news/20191002/murderer-george-brinkman-no-excuses-give-me-death|title=Murderer George Brinkman: No excuses, give me death|first=Ed|last=Balint|date=October 2, 2019|website=indeonline.com}}</ref> He formerly dated Gene John's daughter<ref name= \":13\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.the-review.com/news/20191003/stark-county-judges-hand-george-brinkman-two-more-death-sentences|title=Stark County judges hand George Brinkman two more death sentences|first=Ed|last=Balint|date=October 3, 2019|website=the-review.com}}</ref> and lived with her for several years. Brinkman had previously worked for Gene John\u2019s business as a phone book delivery person. He had also worked making furniture out of his garage and as a mechanic.<ref name= \":11\"/>\nRight before the murders, Brinkman was watching the John couple\u2019s home and caring for their seventeen-year-old dog while the couple was away on a beach vacation in [[North Carolina]] with one of Bobbi John\u2019s sons and his children.<ref name= \":13\"/>\n\nBrinkman was found guilty of [[disorderly conduct]] in 1990, [[criminal mischief]] in 1991, and passing bad checks in 1998.<ref name= \":11\"/> He spent time in [[prison]] for his crimes.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.foxnews.com/us/suspect-in-ohio-triple-murder-charged-with-killing-2-others|title=Suspect in Ohio triple murder charged with killing 2 others|date=June 13, 2017|website=foxnews.com}}</ref>\n\n==Murders==\n===North Royalton murders===\n{{Infobox event\n| image = Suzanne Taylor, Taylor Pifer, and Kylie Pifer.jpg\n| title = North Royalton murders\n| date  = June 10, 2017\n| location = [[North Royalton, Ohio]]\n| reported deaths  = Suzanne Taylor, Taylor Pifer, & Kylie Pifer\n| convicted = George Brinkman Jr.\n| sentence = [[Death penalty|Death]]\n| caption = Suzanne Taylor (right) with her daughters, Taylor Pifer (left), and Kylie Pifer (middle)\n}}\nOn June 10, 2017, Brinkman held Taylor and her daughters captive inside their home.<ref name= \":2\"/> Investigators concluded that Brinkman [[Physical restraint|bound]] the women at their wrists and ankles and killed them one by one.<ref name= \":7\"/> Investigators also believe that he cut off Taylor\u2019s flowing long hair which she took pride in.<ref name= \":3\"/> Brinkman first killed Taylor within arms reach of her daughters<ref name= \":7\"/> by [[stabbing]] her in the head and slitting her throat. After murdering their mother in front of them, Brinkman murdered both Pifer sisters. He killed Taylor Pifer by [[smothering]] her with a pillow. He then killed Kylie Pifer by [[strangling]] her with a phone cord.<ref name= \":2\"/> Brinkman placed the victims' bodies in Taylor\u2019s bed and covered them with blankets.<ref name= \":14\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.cantonrep.com/news/20170614/george-c-brinkman-jr-now-charged-with-5-deaths|title=George C. Brinkman Jr. now charged with 5 deaths|first=Lori|last=Steineck|date=June 14, 2017|website=cantonrep.com}}</ref><ref name= \":7\"/> He fled to the Johns' home in [[Stark County, Ohio]].<ref name= \":7\"/>\n\n===Lake Township murders===\n{{Infobox event\n| image = Gene and Bobbi John.jpg\n| title = Lake Township murders\n| date  = June 11, 2017\n| location = [[Lake Township, Ohio]]\n| reported deaths  = Rogell \"Gene\" John & Roberta \"Bobbi\" John\n| convicted = George Brinkman Jr.\n| sentence = [[Death penalty|Death]]\n}}\nWhen at the Johns\u2019 home, Brinkman got out Gene John\u2019s [[.45 ACP|.45 caliber]] [[handgun]] and loaded it.<ref name= \":13\"/> According to his [[interrogation]], Mrs. John accused him of not giving their deaf-blind dog its medication, leading to an argument.<ref name= \":1\"/><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cleveland19.com/2019/10/03/inside-convicted-killer-george-brinkmans-confession-killing-stark-county-couple/|title=Inside convicted killer George Brinkman\u2019s confession to killing Stark County couple|first=Sara|last= Goldenberg|date=October 2, 2019|website=cleveland19.com}}</ref> After Mr. John questioned him about the gun Brinkman says he ordered the couple to an upstairs bedroom. [[Prosecutors]] would later argue that Brinkman chose that specific bedroom because it was farthest away from the neighbors.<ref name= \":2\"/> The Johns locked the door so Brinkman shot at the doorknob to enter the room. He shot Mr. John three times and struck Mrs. John in the head with the gun, [[Bone fracture|fracturing]] her skull. He also shot Mrs. John twice. Brinkman then stole $40 from Mr. John\u2019s wallet and $100 from Mrs. John\u2019s purse so that he could flee the state.<ref name= \":12\"/>\n\n==Investigation and arrest==\nOn June 12, 2017, Taylor Pifer\u2019s boyfriend became worried when he couldn't reach her on her phone. He went to her house, where he noticed that Suzanne Taylor\u2019s bedroom door, which was always open, was shut. Upon opening the bedroom door, he found the three deceased women in the bed under a blanket. The police were called<ref name= \":7\"/> and responded, finding the three women \"face down in bed all lying right next to one another.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cbsnews.com/news/slain-mother-daughters-were-found-face-down-in-bed-suspect-charged/ |title=Slain mother, daughters were found \"face down in bed\"; suspect charged|date=June 14, 2017|website=cbsnews.com}}</ref>\nAfter finding the women's bodies, Pifer\u2019s boyfriend called Brinkman to inform him. He reported that Brinkman seemed surprised and genuinely sad upon hearing about the deaths. Family and friends of Taylor and the Pifers and police later found Taylor\u2019s hair around the house. This led investigators to believe that Brinkman cut off Taylor\u2019s hair before killing her.<ref name= \":3\"/>\n\nThe Johns' bodies were discovered on June 12 by Mr. John\u2019s son, who had gone to check on them when his father didn't show up to work. Like Taylor and her daughters, the Johns were covered with blankets.<ref name= \":10\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.dispatch.com/news/20170613/suspect-in-stark-county-double-homicide-was-house-sitting-for-victims|title=Suspect in Stark County double homicide was house-sitting for victims|first=Lori|last=Steineck|date=June 13, 2017|website=dispatch.com}}</ref><ref name= \":1\"/><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://abcnews.go.com/US/ohio-man-accused-killing-allegedly-strangled-18-year/story?id=48060033|title=Ohio man accused of killing 5 allegedly strangled 18-year-old victim with telephone cord|first1=Emily|last1=Shapiro|first2=Jason|last2=Volack|date=\nJune 15, 2017|website=abcnews}}</ref>\n\nAfter committing the murders, Brinkman went to the home of a woman he knew in [[Brunswick, Ohio]]. There, he started a police standoff, during which he spoke on [[Facebook]] to a TV reporter about the murders.<ref name= \":14\"/> The standoff lasted nine hours, beginning at 9:30 pm on June 12 and ending at 5:30 am the next day. A [[SWAT]] team surrounded the house and officers entered, finding Brinkman armed with a gun. They subdued him with a [[Electroshock weapon|stun gun]] and arrested him.<ref name= \":15\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.cleveland.com/north-royalton/2017/06/north_royalton_mothers_throat.html |title=North Royalton woman's throat slit, daughters suffocated and strangled in brutal killings, judge says|first=Evan|last=MacDonald|date= June 15, 2017|website=cleveland.com}}</ref> When taken into custody, Brinkman was in possession of evidence linking him to the murders of the Johns.<ref name= \":10\"/> He confessed to killing the Johns and to throwing evidence out of a vehicle window while on [[Interstate 77]] in [[Summit County, Ohio|Summit County]].<ref name= \":1\"/> Brinkman was held in jail on a 75 million dollar bond.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cleveland.com/metro/2017/06/son_of_slain_stark_county_coup.html|title=Son of slain Stark County couple 'heartbroken' over their death|first=Kaylee|last=Remington|date=June 16, 2017|website=cleveland.com}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://myfox28columbus.com/news/local/75m-bond-set-for-ohio-man-accused-of-killing-5-people|title=$75M bond set for Ohio man accused of killing 5 people|date=June 15, 2017|website=myfox28columbus.com}}</ref>\n\n==Criminal proceedings==\n===Criminal proceedings regarding the North Royalton murders===\nOn November 5, 2018, Brinkman pleaded guilty to the North Royalton murders. He also waived his right to a jury. [[Judge|Judges]] Peter Corrigan, Michael Shaughnessy and Timothy McCormick<ref name= \":3\"/>\nofficially found him guilty of murdering Taylor and the Pifers on November 26.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.wkyc.com/article/news/crime/judge-panel-finds-george-brinkman-guilty-of-3-murders-death-penalty-remains-on-table/95-617762483|title=Judge panel finds George Brinkman guilty of 3 murders; death penalty remains on table|date=November 26, 2018|website=wkyc.com}}</ref> Though Brinkman\u2019s [[Criminal defense lawyer|defense attorneys]] offered for him to plead guilty in exchange for a sentence of [[life without parole]], [[District Attorney]] Michael O\u2019Malley and his office refused to drop their pursuit of the death penalty.<ref name= \":3\"/>\n\nOn November 27, the judges found that Brinkman should face the death penalty for the murder of Taylor and her daughters.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://apnews.com/3a8d79361d424e0eb9776f447ea57baf |title=Man convicted in slayings faces death penalty at sentencing|date=November 27, 2018|website=apnews.com}}</ref> Brinkman\u2019s attorneys argued that he should be sentenced to life without parole due to the [[mitigating factors]].<ref name= \":6\"/> Brinkman was formally sentenced to death for the murders on December 28.<ref name= \":2\"/>\nDuring his [[victim impact statement]], Taylor and Kylie Pifer\u2019s father Brian Pifer said: \n<blockquote><p> \u201cFor nearly a year and a half now I\u2019ve been attending all of these pre-trial hearings, reading all the motions filed by the defendant, each arguing that he has specific rights...but today I\u2019m asking you honorable judges to be the voices for the rights taken by Mr. George Brinkman Jr. The right of Taylor to finish her last year at Kent State University. The right of Taylor to graduate, to get a job in the fashion industry that she was so passionate about, to get her first apartment, her first car, her first house. Taylor\u2019s right to get married, to have children, to celebrate the holidays, her right to play another game of softball and sing in the car and go to concerts. Kylie\u2019s right to become a forensic scientist that she always wanted to be, to finish her education at BGSU and to get her masters that she had planned on....her right to get married and have children and all of our rights to a part of those things.\u201d<ref name= \"Father's victim impact statement\">{{Cite YouTube|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=kP2SLZGyUUY|title=GEORGE BRINKMAN SENTENCED|time=4m30s}}</ref></p></blockquote>\nMr. Pifer also said:\n<blockquote><p> \u201cThe rhetoric used by the defense in the entire second half of these proceedings was meant to diminish the impact of the crimes, referring to them as \u2018a situation, an event, an incident.' That is not accepting responsibility for what you have done. The reality is that George Brinkman Jr. took from all three of them the very right to breathe when he carried out his plan last June, when he brutally murdered Taylor, Kylie, and Suzanne. When he bound them, murdering them one by one, he didn\u2019t show any mercy. Yet he has the audacity to ask this court, you, for mercy on him. They (the victims) didn't deserve this. That's why I am asking you to be the three voices for the three lost. I\u2019m asking you to remember all the testimony that you heard and all the rights Mr. Brinkman ripped from them, from all of us.\"<ref name = \"Father's victim impact statement\"/></p></blockquote>\n \nO'Malley said of Brinkman's death sentence \u201cif there's an individual who deserved the death penalty it was George Brinkman who, over the span of two days, murdered five people,\u201d<ref name= \":6\"/> and that \"Brinkman is a mass murderer who should quickly be executed.\" Brinkman's execution date was set for January 15, 2020.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.news5cleveland.com/news/local-news/oh-cuyahoga/man-who-pleaded-guilty-to-killing-woman-2-daughters-expected-to-be-sentenced-to-death-friday|title=Man who murdered North Royalton mother and her 2 daughters sentenced to death|first=Ian|last=Cross|date=December 28, 2018|website=news5cleveland.com}}</ref> In addition to his death sentence, Brinkman was sentenced to forty-seven years in prison.<ref name= \":6\"/>\n\n===Criminal proceedings regarding the Lake Township murders===\nIn October 2019 Brinkman pleaded guilty to the [[aggravated]] murder of the John couple.<ref name= \":4\"/> Though Brinkman plead guilty, a trial was conducted because he faced the death penalty.<ref name= \":13\"/> After deliberating for thirty minutes Judges Chryssa Harnett, Kristin Farmer, and Taryn Heath found Brinkman guilty of all charges regarding the couple\u2019s deaths.<ref name= \":1\"/> During the sentencing phase, defense counsel argued that Brinkman\u2019s life should be spared due to his history of homelessness and mental health problems, and his childhood.<ref name= \":13\"/> Brinkman, however, argued in favor of his own death sentence. He said in a statement \u201cthey (his victims) were extremely kind, caring and wonderful and people who did not deserve to be killed by me.\u201d He also said that he was \u201cso very sorry for all the pain and suffering I have caused the families and friends of Gene and Bobbi. I know that will never be enough but it\u2019s all I have.\u201d In regards to the mitigating circumstances, Brinkman said \u201cyes, I had a horrible childhood ... yes, I\u2019ve had a lot of bad things happen to me in my life, so what? Other (people have) had it worse and never went around killing people they care about.\u201d<ref name= \":12\"/>\n\nJudges Harnett, Farmer and Heath agreed with Brinkman and the prosecution and sentenced Brinkman to death on October 4. In her victim impact statement, Mrs. John\u2019s sister told Brinkman \u201cyou are a monster, a vile evil being that deserves to be put to death.\" Mr. John\u2019s granddaughter said \u201cmy opinion of you has somewhat changed. I decided to not let the anger and hate that I felt for you consume me. I do not hate you, though I thought you were a good man and that is why grandpa and bobby had faith in you. All I want for you in exchange for my forgiveness is the facts, but that is something we will never know.\"<ref name= \":5\"/>\n\n===Incarceration status===\nBrinkman is currently on death row at the Chillicothe Correctional Institution in Chillicothe, Ohio.<ref name= \"ODRC\"/>\n\n== References ==\n<!-- Inline citations added to your article will automatically display here. See en.wikipedia.org/wiki/WP:REFB for instructions on how to add citations. -->\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:George, Brinkman Jr.}}\n[[Category:Crime]]\n[[Category:2017 murders in the United States]]\n[[Category:June 2017 events in the United States]]\n[[Category:Kidnappings in the United States]]\n[[Category:Incidents of violence against women]]\n[[Category:American spree killers]]\n", "text_old": "'''George Brinkman Jr.''' (born 1972) is an American [[murderer]] who took the lives of five people during a 2017 [[killing spree]].<ref name= \"ODRC\"/><ref name= \":1\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.beaconjournal.com/news/20191001/george-brinkman-jr-found-guilty-in-lake-township-slayings|title=George Brinkman Jr. found guilty in Lake Township slayings|first=Ed|last=Balint|date=October 1, 2019|website=beaconjournal.com}}</ref> His first victims were Suzanne Taylor, with whom he had been friends since elementary school, and her two daughters, twenty-one-year-old Taylor Pifer and eighteen-year-old Kylie Pifer. On June 10, 2017, Brinkman took the women [[Captivity|captive]] inside their home in [[North Royalton, Ohio]]. He killed Taylor in front of her daughters before killing them as well.<ref name= \":2\">{{cite press release |date= December 28, 2018|title= George Brinkman Sentenced to Death for the Murders of 45-year-old Suzanne Taylor, and her two daughters, Taylor Pifer, 21, and Kylie Pifer, 18|url=http://prosecutor.cuyahogacounty.us/en-US/2018-12-28-pr-George-Brinkman-Sentenced-to-Death.aspx |agency=Cuyahoga County Office of the Prosecutor}}</ref> Brinkman then went to the [[Lake Township, Ohio]] home of seventy-one-year-old Rogell \u201cGene\u201d John and his sixty-four-year-old wife Roberta \u201cBobbi\u201d John. Brinkman, who had known the couple for over ten years, [[Gunshot wound|shot]] them both to death.<ref name= \":1\"/>\n\nBrinkman [[pleaded guilty]] to the North Royalton murders in November 2018 and to the Lake Township murders in October 2019.<ref name= \":3\"/><ref name= \":4\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.wkyc.com/article/news/crime/man-who-pleaded-guilty-in-north-royalton-slayings-pleads-guilty-to-two-more-in-stark-county/95-9f750169-0260-45bc-9e87-8885dfede17d|title=Man who pleaded guilty in 3 North Royalton slayings, pleads guilty for 2 more in Stark County|date=October 2, 2019|website=wkyc.com}}</ref> He was [[sentenced to death]] for murdering Taylor and her daughters in December 2018.<ref name= \":2\"/> In October 2019 he received another death sentence for murdering the Johns.<ref name= \":5\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.cleveland19.com/2019/10/04/convicted-killer-receive-sentencing-after-admitting-additional-murders/ |title=Convicted killer receives death sentence for murdering Stark County couple|first=Alan|last= Rodges|date=October 4, 2019|website=cleveland19.com}}</ref> Brinkman is currently on [[death row]] at the [[Chillicothe Correctional Institution]] in [[Chillicothe, Ohio]].<ref name= \"ODRC\"/>\n\n==Background==\n===Victims===\nSuzanne Taylor was from [[Parma Heights, Ohio]]. She graduated from [[Valley Forge High School]] in 1990<ref name= \"Heavy\">{{Cite web|url=https://heavy.com/news/2017/06/suzanne-taylor-kylie-pifer-north-royalton-ohio-mother-daughters-murder-photos/|title=Suzanne Taylor, Kylie & Taylor Pifer: 5 Fast Facts You Need to Know|first=Tom|last=Cleary|date=Jun 13, 2017|website=heavy.com}}</ref> and went on to attend [[Hiram College]] where she earned a bachelor of arts degree in [[psychology]], [[sociology]], and [[political science]]. She worked as an administrator at REO Property Consultants, starting in 2012, and as a [[real estate appraiser]] for Forsythe Appraisals, starting in 2013.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.linkedin.com/in/suzanne-taylor-2ab69551|title=Suzanne Taylor|website=linkedin.com}}</ref> Taylor lived in the [[Cleveland]] suburb of North Royalton, Ohio, with her two daughters, Kylie Pifer, eighteen, and Taylor Pifer, twenty-one.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.10tv.com/article/ohio-man-convicted-3-killings-set-trial-2-more-2019-may|title=Ohio man convicted in 3 killings is set for trial in 2 more|date=May 6, 2019|website=10tv.com}}</ref><ref name= \":6\">{{Cite web|url=https://fox8.com/news/man-accused-of-killing-north-royalton-family-to-be-sentenced-friday/|title=Man who killed North Royalton family sentenced to death penalty|first1=Natasha|last1=Anderson| first2=Matt|last2=Wright|date=December 28, 2018|website=fox8.com}}</ref> Taylor Pifer was a 2014 graduate of [[North Royalton High School]] and had just completed her junior year at [[Kent State University]]. She played softball while in high school and worked at the Kent State Fashion Management Store while in college.<ref name= \"Heavy\"/> She was working towards obtaining a bachelors degree in [[fashion design]] and [[merchandising]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.wayup.com/profile/Taylor-Pifer-37688a0b07/|title=Taylor Pifer|website=wayup.com}}</ref> Kylie Pifer was set to begin her sophomore year at [[Bowling Green State University]] in the fall of 2017.  She was involved in theater and studied [[biology]],<ref name= \"Heavy\"/> and aspired to become a [[forensic scientist]].<ref name= \":7\"/> She would have turned nineteen on Sunday, June 18, 2017.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.kentwired.com/latest_updates/article_1777830c-5184-11e7-a732-4fec2ca0ab71.html|title=Community mourns slain student, family at candlelight vigil|first=Elizabeth|last=Harrington|date=June 15, 2017|website=kentwired.com}}</ref>\n\nRogell E. \u201cGene\u201d John II (born 1945) was a graduate of [[East Canton High School]] and Bowling Green State University.<ref name= \":8\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.sandersfuneralhomes.com/obituary/Rogell-John|title=Rogell E. \"Gene\" John|website=sandersfuneralhomes.com}}</ref> He was also a [[Vietnam War veteran]]. Mr. John worked in the circulation department of [[The Canton Repository]] and served as the circulation director at The Massillon Independent and GateHouse Ohio. He then started his own business distributing telephone books and publications.<ref name= \":9\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.indeonline.com/news/20191003/stark-county-judges-hand-george-brinkman-two-more-death-sentences|title=George BrinkmanStark County judges hand George Brinkman two more death sentences|first=Ed|last=Balint|date=October 3, 2019|website=indeonline.com}}</ref><ref name= \":10\"/> He was married to Roberta R. \u201cBobbi\u201d John (born 1952), a [[North Canton Hoover High School]], [[Ohio University]] and [[Akron University]] graduate. Before retirement, Mrs. John worked as the Director of Special Services for [[Stow-Munroe Falls City School District]].<ref name= \"Legacy Bobbi\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.legacy.com/obituaries/cantonrep/obituary.aspx?n=roberta-r-bobbi-john&pid=185844075&fhid=6475|title=Roberta R. Bobbi JOHN|website=legacy.com}}</ref> She also worked for the [[Alliance, Ohio|Alliance]] and [[Louisville, Ohio|Louisville]] school districts.<ref name= \":9\"/> Both Mr. and Mrs. John were active members of  Mt. Tabor United Methodist Church, the Osnaburg Historical Society.<ref name= \"Legacy Bobbi\"/><ref name= \":8\"/> The couple lived in Lake Township, Ohio.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://abc6onyourside.com/news/local/man-argues-for-his-own-death-sentence-in-couples-slaying |title=Man argues for his own death sentence in couple's slaying|date=October 3, 2019|website=abc6onyourside.com}}</ref>\n\n===Perpetrator===\nGeorge Brinkman (born 1972)<ref name= \"ODRC\">{{Cite web|url=https://appgateway.drc.ohio.gov/OffenderSearch/Search/Details/A764906|title=Offender Details}}</ref> knew all of his victims well.<ref name= \":11\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.news5cleveland.com/news/local-news/oh-stark/who-is-george-brinkman-suspect-in-the-lake-township-and-north-royalton-homicides|title=Who is George Brinkman? Suspect in the Lake Township and North Royalton homicides|first1=Megan|last1=Hickey|first2=Courtney |last2=Danser|date=June 13, 2017|website=news5cleveland.com}}</ref> He went to elementary school with Suzanne Taylor and remained friends with her through adulthood.<ref name= \":7\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.cleveland.com/court-justice/2018/12/george-brinkman-jr-sentenced-to-death-in-slayings-of-north-royalton-woman-daughters.html|title=George Brinkman Jr. sentenced to death in slayings of North Royalton woman, daughters|first=Cory|last=Shaffter|date=December 28, 2018 |website=cleveland.com}}</ref> Neighbors of Taylor and the Pifer sisters say that Brinkman often visited their home.<ref name= \":11\"/> Taylor let Brinkman do various jobs around her house and also allowed him to sleep in her house during times when he was [[homeless]].<ref name= \":7\"/> Taylor's family believes that Brinkman wanted to be \u201cmore than friends\u201d with her.<ref name= \":6\"/> According to witnesses, the Pifer women looked up to Brinkman like a \u201csecond father.\u201d<ref name= \":3\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.cleveland.com/court-justice/2018/11/north-royalton-man-admits-killing-woman-daughters-as-judges-hear-evidence-in-potential-death-penalty-case.html|title=North Royalton man admits killing woman, daughters, as judges hear evidence in potential death-penalty case|first=Cory|last=Shaffer|date=November 5, 2018|website=cleveland.com}}</ref>\n\nBrinkman knew the John couple for more than ten years.<ref name= \":12\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.indeonline.com/news/20191002/murderer-george-brinkman-no-excuses-give-me-death|title=Murderer George Brinkman: No excuses, give me death|first=Ed|last=Balint|date=October 2, 2019|website=indeonline.com}}</ref> He formerly dated Gene John's daughter<ref name= \":13\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.the-review.com/news/20191003/stark-county-judges-hand-george-brinkman-two-more-death-sentences|title=Stark County judges hand George Brinkman two more death sentences|first=Ed|last=Balint|date=October 3, 2019|website=the-review.com}}</ref> and lived with her for several years. Brinkman had previously worked for Gene John\u2019s business as a phone book delivery person. He had also worked making furniture out of his garage and as a mechanic.<ref name= \":11\"/>\nRight before the murders, Brinkman was watching the John couple\u2019s home and caring for their seventeen-year-old dog while the couple was away on a beach vacation in [[North Carolina]] with one of Bobbi John\u2019s sons and his children.<ref name= \":13\"/>\n\nBrinkman was found guilty of [[disorderly conduct]] in 1990, [[criminal mischief]] in 1991, and passing bad checks in 1998.<ref name= \":11\"/> He spent time in [[prison]] for his crimes.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.foxnews.com/us/suspect-in-ohio-triple-murder-charged-with-killing-2-others|title=Suspect in Ohio triple murder charged with killing 2 others|date=June 13, 2017|website=foxnews.com}}</ref>\n\n==Murders==\n===North Royalton murders===\n{{Infobox event\n| image = Suzanne Taylor, Taylor Pifer, and Kylie Pifer.jpg\n| title = North Royalton murders\n| date  = June 10, 2017\n| location = [[North Royalton, Ohio]]\n| reported deaths  = Suzanne Taylor, Taylor Pifer, & Kylie Pifer\n| convicted = George Brinkman Jr.\n| sentence = [[Death penalty|Death]]\n| caption = Suzanne Taylor (right) with her daughters, Taylor Pifer (left), and Kylie Pifer (middle)\n}}\nOn June 10, 2017, Brinkman held Taylor and her daughters captive inside their home.<ref name= \":2\"/> Investigators concluded that Brinkman [[Physical restraint|bound]] the women at their wrists and ankles and killed them one by one.<ref name= \":7\"/> Investigators also believe that he cut off Taylor\u2019s flowing long hair which she took pride in.<ref name= \":3\"/> Brinkman first killed Taylor within arms reach of her daughters<ref name= \":7\"/> by [[stabbing]] her in the head and slitting her throat. After murdering their mother in front of them, Brinkman murdered both Pifer sisters. He killed Taylor Pifer by [[smothering]] her with a pillow. He then killed Kylie Pifer by [[strangling]] her with a phone cord.<ref name= \":2\"/> Brinkman placed the victims' bodies in Taylor\u2019s bed and covered them with blankets.<ref name= \":14\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.cantonrep.com/news/20170614/george-c-brinkman-jr-now-charged-with-5-deaths|title=George C. Brinkman Jr. now charged with 5 deaths|first=Lori|last=Steineck|date=June 14, 2017|website=cantonrep.com}}</ref><ref name= \":7\"/> He fled to the Johns' home in [[Stark County, Ohio]].<ref name= \":7\"/>\n\n===Lake Township murders===\n{{Infobox event\n| image = Gene and Bobbi John.jpg\n| title = Lake Township murders\n| date  = June 11, 2017\n| location = [[Lake Township, Ohio]]\n| reported deaths  = Rogell \"Gene\" John & Roberta \"Bobbi\" John\n| convicted = George Brinkman Jr.\n| sentence = [[Death penalty|Death]]\n}}\nWhen at the Johns\u2019 home, Brinkman got out Gene John\u2019s [[.45 ACP|.45 caliber]] [[handgun]] and loaded it.<ref name= \":13\"/> According to his [[interrogation]], Mrs. John accused him of not giving their deaf-blind dog its medication, leading to an argument.<ref name= \":1\"/><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cleveland19.com/2019/10/03/inside-convicted-killer-george-brinkmans-confession-killing-stark-county-couple/|title=Inside convicted killer George Brinkman\u2019s confession to killing Stark County couple|first=Sara|last= Goldenberg|date=October 2, 2019|website=cleveland19.com}}</ref> After Mr. John questioned him about the gun Brinkman says he ordered the couple to an upstairs bedroom. [[Prosecutors]] would later argue that Brinkman chose that specific bedroom because it was farthest away from the neighbors.<ref name= \":2\"/> The Johns locked the door so Brinkman shot at the doorknob to enter the room. He shot Mr. John three times and struck Mrs. John in the head with the gun, [[Bone fracture|fracturing]] her skull. He also shot Mrs. John twice. Brinkman then stole $40 from Mr. John\u2019s wallet and $100 from Mrs. John\u2019s purse so that he could flee the state.<ref name= \":12\"/>\n\n==Investigation and arrest==\nOn June 12, 2017, Taylor Pifer\u2019s boyfriend became worried when he couldn't reach her on her phone. He went to her house, where he noticed that Suzanne Taylor\u2019s bedroom door, which was always open, was shut. Upon opening the bedroom door, he found the three deceased women in the bed under a blanket. The police were called<ref name= \":7\"/> and responded, finding the three women \"face down in bed all lying right next to one another.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cbsnews.com/news/slain-mother-daughters-were-found-face-down-in-bed-suspect-charged/ |title=Slain mother, daughters were found \"face down in bed\"; suspect charged|date=June 14, 2017|website=cbsnews.com}}</ref>\nAfter finding the women's bodies, Pifer\u2019s boyfriend called Brinkman to inform him. He reported that Brinkman seemed surprised and genuinely sad upon hearing about the deaths. Family and friends of Taylor and the Pifers and police later found Taylor\u2019s hair around the house. This led investigators to believe that Brinkman cut off Taylor\u2019s hair before killing her.<ref name= \":3\"/>\n\nThe Johns' bodies were discovered on June 12 by Mr. John\u2019s son, who had gone to check on them when his father didn't show up to work. Like Taylor and her daughters, the Johns were covered with blankets.<ref name= \":10\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.dispatch.com/news/20170613/suspect-in-stark-county-double-homicide-was-house-sitting-for-victims|title=Suspect in Stark County double homicide was house-sitting for victims|first=Lori|last=Steineck|date=June 13, 2017|website=dispatch.com}}</ref><ref name= \":1\"/><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://abcnews.go.com/US/ohio-man-accused-killing-allegedly-strangled-18-year/story?id=48060033|title=Ohio man accused of killing 5 allegedly strangled 18-year-old victim with telephone cord|first1=Emily|last1=Shapiro|first2=Jason|last2=Volack|date=\nJune 15, 2017|website=abcnews}}</ref>\n\nAfter committing the murders, Brinkman went to the home of a woman he knew in [[Brunswick, Ohio]]. There, he started a police standoff, during which he spoke on [[Facebook]] to a TV reporter about the murders.<ref name= \":14\"/> The standoff lasted nine hours, beginning at 9:30 pm on June 12 and ending at 5:30 am the next day. A [[SWAT]] team surrounded the house and officers entered, finding Brinkman armed with a gun. They subdued him with a [[stun gun]] and arrested him.<ref name= \":15\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.cleveland.com/north-royalton/2017/06/north_royalton_mothers_throat.html |title=North Royalton woman's throat slit, daughters suffocated and strangled in brutal killings, judge says|first=Evan|last=MacDonald|date= June 15, 2017|website=cleveland.com}}</ref> When taken into custody, Brinkman was in possession of evidence linking him to the murders of the Johns.<ref name= \":10\"/> He confessed to killing the Johns and to throwing evidence out of a vehicle window while on [[Interstate 77]] in [[Summit County, Ohio|Summit County]].<ref name= \":1\"/> Brinkman was held in jail on a 75 million dollar bond.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cleveland.com/metro/2017/06/son_of_slain_stark_county_coup.html|title=Son of slain Stark County couple 'heartbroken' over their death|first=Kaylee|last=Remington|date=June 16, 2017|website=cleveland.com}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://myfox28columbus.com/news/local/75m-bond-set-for-ohio-man-accused-of-killing-5-people|title=$75M bond set for Ohio man accused of killing 5 people|date=June 15, 2017|website=myfox28columbus.com}}</ref>\n\n==Criminal proceedings==\n===Criminal proceedings regarding the North Royalton murders===\nOn November 5, 2018, Brinkman pleaded guilty to the North Royalton murders. He also waived his right to a jury. [[Judge|Judges]] Peter Corrigan, Michael Shaughnessy and Timothy McCormick<ref name= \":3\"/>\nofficially found him guilty of murdering Taylor and the Pifers on November 26.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.wkyc.com/article/news/crime/judge-panel-finds-george-brinkman-guilty-of-3-murders-death-penalty-remains-on-table/95-617762483|title=Judge panel finds George Brinkman guilty of 3 murders; death penalty remains on table|date=November 26, 2018|website=wkyc.com}}</ref> Though Brinkman\u2019s [[Criminal defense lawyer|defense attorneys]] offered for him to plead guilty in exchange for a sentence of [[life without parole]], [[District Attorney]] Michael O\u2019Malley and his office refused to drop their pursuit of the death penalty.<ref name= \":3\"/>\n\nOn November 27, the judges found that Brinkman should face the death penalty for the murder of Taylor and her daughters.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://apnews.com/3a8d79361d424e0eb9776f447ea57baf |title=Man convicted in slayings faces death penalty at sentencing|date=November 27, 2018|website=apnews.com}}</ref> Brinkman\u2019s attorneys argued that he should be sentenced to life without parole due to the [[mitigating factors]].<ref name= \":6\"/> Brinkman was formally sentenced to death for the murders on December 28.<ref name= \":2\"/>\nDuring his [[victim impact statement]], Taylor and Kylie Pifer\u2019s father Brian Pifer said: \n<blockquote><p> \u201cFor nearly a year and a half now I\u2019ve been attending all of these pre-trial hearings, reading all the motions filed by the defendant, each arguing that he has specific rights...but today I\u2019m asking you honorable judges to be the voices for the rights taken by Mr. George Brinkman Jr. The right of Taylor to finish her last year at Kent State University. The right of Taylor to graduate, to get a job in the fashion industry that she was so passionate about, to get her first apartment, her first car, her first house. Taylor\u2019s right to get married, to have children, to celebrate the holidays, her right to play another game of softball and sing in the car and go to concerts. Kylie\u2019s right to become a forensic scientist that she always wanted to be, to finish her education at BGSU and to get her masters that she had planned on....her right to get married and have children and all of our rights to a part of those things.\u201d<ref name= \"Father's victim impact statement\">{{Cite YouTube|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=kP2SLZGyUUY|title=GEORGE BRINKMAN SENTENCED|time=4m30s}}</ref></p></blockquote>\nMr. Pifer also said:\n<blockquote><p> \u201cThe rhetoric used by the defense in the entire second half of these proceedings was meant to diminish the impact of the crimes, referring to them as \u2018a situation, an event, an incident.' That is not accepting responsibility for what you have done. The reality is that George Brinkman Jr. took from all three of them the very right to breathe when he carried out his plan last June, when he brutally murdered Taylor, Kylie, and Suzanne. When he bound them, murdering them one by one, he didn\u2019t show any mercy. Yet he has the audacity to ask this court, you, for mercy on him. They (the victims) didn't deserve this. That's why I am asking you to be the three voices for the three lost. I\u2019m asking you to remember all the testimony that you heard and all the rights Mr. Brinkman ripped from them, from all of us.\"<ref name = \"Father's victim impact statement\"/></p></blockquote>\n \nO'Malley said of Brinkman's death sentence \u201cif there's an individual who deserved the death penalty it was George Brinkman who, over the span of two days, murdered five people,\u201d<ref name= \":6\"/> and that \"Brinkman is a mass murderer who should quickly be executed.\" Brinkman's execution date was set for January 15, 2020.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.news5cleveland.com/news/local-news/oh-cuyahoga/man-who-pleaded-guilty-to-killing-woman-2-daughters-expected-to-be-sentenced-to-death-friday|title=Man who murdered North Royalton mother and her 2 daughters sentenced to death|first=Ian|last=Cross|date=December 28, 2018|website=news5cleveland.com}}</ref> In addition to his death sentence, Brinkman was sentenced to forty-seven years in prison.<ref name= \":6\"/>\n\n===Criminal proceedings regarding the Lake Township murders===\nIn October 2019 Brinkman pleaded guilty to the [[aggravated]] murder of the John couple.<ref name= \":4\"/> Though Brinkman plead guilty, a trial was conducted because he faced the death penalty.<ref name= \":13\"/> After deliberating for thirty minutes Judges Chryssa Harnett, Kristin Farmer, and Taryn Heath found Brinkman guilty of all charges regarding the couple\u2019s deaths.<ref name= \":1\"/> During the sentencing phase, defense counsel argued that Brinkman\u2019s life should be spared due to his history of homelessness and mental health problems, and his childhood.<ref name= \":13\"/> Brinkman, however, argued in favor of his own death sentence. He said in a statement \u201cthey (his victims) were extremely kind, caring and wonderful and people who did not deserve to be killed by me.\u201d He also said that he was \u201cso very sorry for all the pain and suffering I have caused the families and friends of Gene and Bobbi. I know that will never be enough but it\u2019s all I have.\u201d In regards to the mitigating circumstances, Brinkman said \u201cyes, I had a horrible childhood ... yes, I\u2019ve had a lot of bad things happen to me in my life, so what? Other (people have) had it worse and never went around killing people they care about.\u201d<ref name= \":12\"/>\n\nJudges Harnett, Farmer and Heath agreed with Brinkman and the prosecution and sentenced Brinkman to death on October 4. In her victim impact statement, Mrs. John\u2019s sister told Brinkman \u201cyou are a monster, a vile evil being that deserves to be put to death.\" Mr. John\u2019s granddaughter said \u201cmy opinion of you has somewhat changed. I decided to not let the anger and hate that I felt for you consume me. I do not hate you, though I thought you were a good man and that is why grandpa and bobby had faith in you. All I want for you in exchange for my forgiveness is the facts, but that is something we will never know.\"<ref name= \":5\"/>\n\n===Incarceration status===\nBrinkman is currently on death row at the Chillicothe Correctional Institution in Chillicothe, Ohio.<ref name= \"ODRC\"/>\n\n== References ==\n<!-- Inline citations added to your article will automatically display here. See en.wikipedia.org/wiki/WP:REFB for instructions on how to add citations. -->\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:George, Brinkman Jr.}}\n[[Category:Crime]]\n[[Category:2017 murders in the United States]]\n[[Category:June 2017 events in the United States]]\n[[Category:Kidnappings in the United States]]\n[[Category:Incidents of violence against women]]\n[[Category:American spree killers]]\n", "name_user": "Rodw", "label": "safe", "comment": "Disambiguating links toStun gun(link changed toElectroshock weapon) usingDisamAssist.", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/George_Brinkman_murders"}
{"title_page": "2020 in the United Kingdom", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2020}}\n{{EngvarB|date = November 2018}}\n{{Year in United Kingdom|2020|label1=Individual countries of the United Kingdom|data1=[[2020 in England|England]] {{!}} [[2020 in Northern Ireland|Northern Ireland]] {{!}} [[2020 in Scotland|Scotland]] {{!}} [[2020 in Wales|Wales]]|label2=Sport, television and music|data2=<div>\n[[Football in the United Kingdom|Football]]: [[2019\u201320 in English football|England]] {{!}} [[2019\u201320 in Scottish football|Scotland]] {{!}} [[2019\u201320 in Welsh football|Wales]]<br />\n[[2020 British Grand Prix]]<br />\n[[2020 English cricket season]]<br />\n[[2020 in British television]]<br />\n[[2020 in British music]]<br />\n[[2020 in British radio]]<br />\n[[United Kingdom in the Eurovision Song Contest 2020|UK in the Eurovision Song Contest 2020]]\n</div>}}\nEvents from the year '''2020 in the United Kingdom'''.\n\n==Incumbents==\n*[[Monarch of the United Kingdom|Monarch]] \u2013 [[Elizabeth II]]\n*[[Prime Minister of the United Kingdom|Prime Minister]] \u2013 [[Boris Johnson]] ([[Conservative Party (UK)|Conservative]])\n*[[Parliament of the United Kingdom|Parliament]] \u2013 [[List of MPs elected in the 2019 United Kingdom general election|58th]]\n\n== Events ==\n\n=== January ===\n*4 January \u2013 The [[Foreign and Commonwealth Office|Foreign Office]] warns British nationals against all but essential travel to [[Iran]] and [[Iraq]], following [[2020 Baghdad International Airport airstrike|a US airstrike in Baghdad]] the previous day in which Iranian general [[Qasem Soleimani]] was killed.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-politics-50991778 |title=Qasem Soleimani: Foreign Office hardens Iran and Iraq travel advice |work=BBC News |publisher=BBC |date=4 January 2020 |accessdate=5 January 2020}}</ref>\n*5 January \u2013 Boris Johnson says \"we will not lament\" Qasem Soleimani's death as he calls for \"de-escalation from all sides\".<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-51001236 |title=Qasem Soleimani: PM 'will not lament' Iranian general's death |work=BBC News |publisher=BBC |date=5 January 2020 |accessdate=5 January 2020}}</ref>\n*6 January\n**[[Reynhard Sinaga]], described as \"the most prolific rapist in British legal history\", is sentenced to life in prison with a minimum term of 30 years, after being found guilty of raping or sexually assaulting 48 men in Manchester. Police believe he may have been responsible for assaulting a total of nearly 200 victims.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2020/jan/06/reynhard-sinaga-jailed-life-drugging-raping-men-manchester |title=Reynhard Sinaga: man jailed for life for raping dozens of men in Manchester |work=The Guardian|date=6 January 2020 |accessdate=6 January 2020}}</ref>\n**[[Downing Street]] states that Britain will not support U.S. President [[Donald Trump]]'s threat to bomb Iranian cultural and heritage sites.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/jan/06/no-10-uk-would-not-back-us-bombing-of-iranian-cultural-sites|title=UK would not back US bombing of Iran cultural sites \u2013 No 10|work=The Guardian|date=6 January 2020 |accessdate=6 January 2020}}</ref>\n*7 January \u2013 The [[2020 Labour Party leadership election|Labour Party leadership election]] formally begins, with the new leader scheduled to be announced on 4 April.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-politics-51000133 |title=Labour leadership: Result will be announced on 4 April |work=BBC News |publisher=BBC |date=6 January 2020 |accessdate=6 January 2020}}</ref>\n*8 January \u2013 [[Prince Harry, Duke of Sussex]], and [[Meghan, Duchess of Sussex]], announce that they plan to \"step back as senior members\" of [[British Royal family|Britain's royal family]], and divide their time between the UK and North America.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-51040751 |title=Harry and Meghan to step back as senior royals |work=BBC News |publisher=BBC |date=8 January 2020 |accessdate=8 January 2020}}</ref>\n*9 January \n**The [[House of Commons of the United Kingdom|House of Commons]] gives its third and final backing to the [[European Union (Withdrawal Agreement) Bill 2019\u201320|Withdrawal Agreement Bill]], voting 330 to 231 in favour; the bill now passes to the [[House of Lords (United Kingdom)|House of Lords]] for scrutiny.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-politics-51051178 |title=MPs give final backing to Brexit bill |work=BBC News |publisher=BBC |date=9 January 2020 |accessdate=9 January 2020}}</ref>\n**The UK and Irish governments publish [[2020 Northern Ireland Agreement|a deal]] aimed at restoring the [[Northern Ireland Executive]]; the [[Democratic Unionist Party]] gives its backing to the agreement.<ref>{{Cite news|first=Andrew |last=Madden |url=https://www.belfasttelegraph.co.uk/news/northern-ireland/dup-accept-governments-draft-agreement-to-restore-stormont-sinn-fein-studying-text-38849112.html |title=DUP accept governments' draft agreement to restore Stormont, Sinn Fein 'studying' text |work=Belfast Telegraph |publisher=Independent News and Media |date=9 January 2020 |accessdate=12 January 2020}}</ref>\n*10 January \u2013 [[Sinn F\u00e9in]] gives its backing to [[2020 Northern Ireland Agreement|a deal]] to restore power-sharing government to Northern Ireland for the first time since 2017.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-northern-ireland-51068774 |title=Sinn F\u00e9in agrees to rejoin NI government after deal |work=BBC News |publisher=BBC |date=10 January 2020 |accessdate=10 January 2020}}</ref>\n*11 January  \n**The [[Northern Ireland Assembly]] reconvenes after a three-year hiatus; [[Democratic Unionist Party|DUP]] leader [[Arlene Foster]] is appointed [[First Minister of Northern Ireland|Northern Ireland's first minister]], while [[Sinn Fein]]'s [[Michelle O'Neill]] is appointed [[Deputy First Minister of Northern Ireland|deputy first minister]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-northern-ireland-51077397 |title=Stormont deal: Arlene Foster and Michelle O'Neill new top NI ministers |work=BBC News |publisher=BBC |date=11 January 2020 |accessdate=11 January 2020}}</ref>\n**[[Robert Macaire (diplomat)|Robert Macaire]], the British ambassador to [[Iran]], is briefly detained in Iran after attending a vigil for those killed on [[Ukraine International Airlines Flight 752]]. Iran summoned him to appear at [[Ministry of Foreign Affairs (Iran)|its foreign ministry]] the following day after saying he had been \"an unknown foreigner in an illegal gathering\".<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-51077897 |title=Iran plane crash: Britain condemns Tehran's arrest of UK ambassador |work=BBC News |publisher=BBC |date=12 January 2020 |accessdate=12 January 2020}}</ref>\n*13 January \u2013 Following a meeting of senior royals, [[Elizabeth II|the Queen]] agrees to a \"period of transition\" during which the Duke and Duchess of Sussex will spend time in Canada and the UK.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-51099102 |title=Queen agrees 'transition' to new role for Harry and Meghan |work=BBC News |publisher=BBC |date=13 January 2020 |accessdate=14 January 2020}}</ref>\n*14 January\n**The government agrees a rescue package for troubled regional airline [[Flybe]] to stop it going into administration.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/business-51113895 |title=Flybe: Government strikes a deal to rescue troubled airline |work=BBC News |publisher=BBC |date=14 January 2020 |accessdate=14 January 2020}}</ref>\n**Boris Johnson formally rejects [[First Minister of Scotland|Scottish First Minister]] [[Nicola Sturgeon]]'s request for a [[Proposed second Scottish independence referendum|second independence referendum]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-scotland-scotland-politics-51106796 |title=Scottish independence: Johnson rejects Sturgeon's indyref2 demand |work=BBC News |publisher=BBC |date=14 January 2020 |accessdate=15 January 2020}}</ref>\n*16 January \u2013 Legislation is drafted before Parliament allowing the use of [[Professional video camera|television cameras]] during trials at [[Crown Court]]s in England and Wales, but only the [[judge]]s will be filmed.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-51110206 |title=TV cameras to be allowed in Crown Courts in England and Wales |work=BBC News |publisher=BBC |date=16 January 2020 |accessdate=16 January 2020}}</ref>\n*17 January \u2013 Construction begins on [[Dogger Bank Wind Farm]], which will become the world's largest offshore wind farm when complete, with 260-metre high turbines generating a combined 3.6 gigawatts and supplying 4.5 million homes.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.cnbc.com/amp/2020/01/17/work-starts-on-huge-wind-farm-that-could-power-4point5-million-homes.html |title=Work starts on world's 'largest offshore wind farm' that could power 4.5 million homes|publisher=CNBC|date=17 January 2020 |accessdate=20 January 2020}}</ref>\n*18 January \u2013 [[Buckingham Palace]] confirms that from spring 2020 the Duke and Duchess of Sussex will no longer use their royal titles and will no longer receive public funds for their royal duties.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-51163865 |title=Harry and Meghan lose funding and drop HRH titles |work=BBC News |publisher=BBC |date=18 January 2020 |accessdate=18 January 2020}}</ref>\n*21 January \u2013 The [[Office of Rail and Road]] announces that [[Network Rail]] is being investigated over its poor performance on routes used by train operators [[Arriva Rail North]] and [[TransPennine Express]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://news.sky.com/story/network-rail-being-investigated-for-poor-performance-11914036 |title=Network Rail being investigated for 'poor performance' |publisher=Sky News|date=21 January 2020 |accessdate=21 January 2020}}</ref>\n*22 January \u2013 Boris Johnson's EU withdrawal deal successfully completes its passage through parliament, with the [[European Union (Withdrawal Agreement) Act 2020|EU Withdrawal Agreement Bill]] being voted through without change, after several amendments proposed by the House of Lords are rejected.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-politics-51214761 |title=Brexit: UK has 'crossed Brexit finish line', says Boris Johnson |date=22 January 2020 |work=BBC News}}</ref>\n*23 January\n**Parliamentary ratification of Boris Johnson's EU withdrawal deal is completed with [[Royal Assent]] being given to the [[European Union (Withdrawal Agreement) Act 2020|EU Withdrawal Agreement Bill]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.europarl.europa.eu/news/en/press-room/20200123IPR70904/brexit-the-withdrawal-agreement-passes-the-first-european-parliament-test |title=Brexit: the Withdrawal Agreement passes the first European Parliament test |date=23 January 2020 |work=News |publisher=European Parliament}}</ref>\n**An [[2002 Dudley earthquake|earthquake]] of 3.0 magnitude is recorded by the [[British Geological Survey]] in [[Stockton-on-Tees]], [[County Durham]], just before 6am.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2020/jan/23/teesside-shaken-by-earthquake-stockton-durham |title=Teesside shaken by 3.0-magnitude earthquake |work=The Guardian|date=23 January 2020 |accessdate=23 January 2020}}</ref>\n*24 January\n**The UK's EU withdrawal agreement is signed by both parties; firstly in the morning in [[Brussels]], by [[European Council]] president [[Charles Michel]] and [[European Commission]] president [[Ursula von der Leyen]] for the EU, then after travelling on the [[Eurostar]] in a diplomatic case, in [[London]] in the afternoon by Prime Minister [[Boris Johnson]] for the UK.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-politics-51244126 |title=Brexit: Boris Johnson signs withdrawal agreement in Downing Street |date=24 January 2020 |work=BBC News}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2020/jan/24/sombre-eu-leaders-sign-brexit-withdrawal-agreement |title='Fantastic moment': Boris Johnson signs Brexit withdrawal deal |date=24 January 2020 |last1=Proctor |first1=Kate |last2=Boffey |first2=Daniel |work=The Guardian}}</ref>\n**Police announce that live [[Facial recognition system|facial recognition technology]] will be rolled out across London.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://uk.reuters.com/article/uk-britain-security-cameras/police-to-roll-out-live-facial-recognition-cameras-in-london-idUKKBN1ZN1H5 |title=Police to roll out live facial recognition cameras in London |publisher=Reuters|date=24 January 2020 |accessdate=24 January 2020}}</ref>\n*25 January \u2013 A newly-appointed member of the [[Grenfell Tower Inquiry|Grenfell Tower fire public enquiry panel]] resigns after being linked to the company which supplied cladding for the block.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-51252297 |title=Grenfell Tower inquiry member Benita Mehra resigns |work=BBC News |publisher=BBC |date=25 January 2020 |accessdate=29 January 2020}}</ref>\n*27 January \u2013 The Health Secretary, [[Matt Hancock]], tells the House of Commons that 200 British citizens trapped in [[Wuhan]], [[China]], will be offered repatriation to the UK, in light of the [[2019\u201320 coronavirus outbreak in Hubei|coronavirus outbreak there]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2020/jan/27/britons-in-wuhan-will-be-offered-help-to-leave-hancock-tells-mps |title=Britons in Wuhan will be offered help to leave, Hancock tells MPs |work=The Guardian|date=27 January 2020 |accessdate=27 January 2020}}</ref>\n*28 January \u2013 The Prime Minister approves a limited \"non-core\" role for China's [[Huawei]] in Britain's [[5G]] mobile network, resisting U.S. pressure to exclude the company on fears China could use it to steal data.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/technology/2020/jan/28/boris-johnson-gives-green-light-for-huawei-5g-infrastructure-role |title=Boris Johnson gives green light for Huawei 5G infrastructure role |work=The Guardian|date=28 January 2020 |accessdate=28 January 2020}}</ref>\n*29 January\n**[[British Airways]] suspends all flights to and from mainland China with immediate effect, due to the ongoing coronavirus threat.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/jan/29/evacuation-of-britons-in-coronavirus-hit-hubei-could-begin-thursday |title=Britons evacuated due to coronavirus to be quarantined |publisher=Guardian Media Group |newspaper==The Guardian |date=29 January 2020 |accessdate=29 January 2020}}</ref>\n**Transport Secretary [[Grant Shapps]] announces that troubled train operator [[Arriva Rail North]] will be brought under government control from 1 March following a prolonged period of delays and poor performance.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-england-51298820 |title=Troubled rail firm Northern brought under government control |work=BBC News |publisher=BBC |date=29 January 2020 |accessdate=29 January 2020}}</ref>\n**''[[The Guardian]]'' announces that it will no longer accept advertising from oil and gas companies, becoming the first major global news organisation to institute an outright ban on taking money from the fossil fuel industry.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/media/2020/jan/29/guardian-to-ban-advertising-from-fossil-fuel-firms-climate-crisis |title=Guardian to ban advertising from fossil fuel firms |publisher=Guardian Media Group |newspaper=The Guardian |date=29 January 2020 |accessdate=29 January 2020}}</ref>\n** The [[European Parliament]] ratifies the [[Brexit withdrawal agreement]] in Brussels, ensuring that if the United Kingdom leaves the European Union, as scheduled, at 23:00 GMT on 31 January 2020, they will do so with a deal.<ref>{{cite news|title=Brexit: European Parliament overwhelmingly backs terms of UK's exit|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-politics-51287430|work=BBC News|publisher=BBC|date=29 January 2020}}</ref>\n*31 January\n**[[COVID-19 in the UK]]: The first two cases of [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in the United Kingdom|coronavirus (2019-nCoV) in the United Kingdom]] are confirmed.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/health-51325192|title=Two coronavirus cases confirmed in UK|date=2020-01-31|work=BBC News|access-date=2020-02-02|language=en-GB}}</ref>\n**The United Kingdom and [[Gibraltar]] leave the [[European Union]],<ref>{{cite news |title=Brexit: UK leaves the European Union |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-politics-51333314 |work=BBC News |publisher=BBC |date=31 January 2019}}</ref> beginning an 11-month transition period, during which they remain in the Single Market and Customs Union.\n\n===February===\n*1 February \u2013 [[Austria]], [[Germany]], and [[Slovenia]] confirm they will not extradite their nationals if they are accused of crimes in the UK.<ref>[https://news.yahoo.com/three-european-countries-refuse-uk-130000250.html Three European countries say they will refuse UK extradition requests now Brexit has happened] by Thomas Colson, Business Insider, 1 February 2020</ref>\n*2 February \u2013 A man is shot dead by police in South London after a [[2020 Streatham stabbing|stabbing incident]] on [[Streatham High Road]]; police treat the incident as [[Terrorism in the United Kingdom|terrorist]]-related.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-england-london-51349664 |title=Streatham attack: Man shot dead by police after stabbings in London |work=BBC News |publisher=BBC |date=2 February 2020 |accessdate=2 February 2020}}</ref>\n*4 February \u2013 In London, Prime Minister Boris Johnson, naturalist [[David Attenborough|Sir David Attenborough]], and Italian Prime Minister [[Giuseppe Conte]] launch the [[COP26|26th session of the Conference of the Parties]] (COP26), a major UN climate summit to be held in Glasgow in November 2020.<ref name=BBC_51366123/> Johnson announces, subject to consultation, that coal power could be phased out by 2024, a year earlier than previously planned and the phase-out of new petrol and diesel vehicles could be brought forward from 2040 to 2035.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/politics/2020/02/04/coal-power-phased-2024-boris-johnson-says-uk-has-duty-fight/|title=Coal power to be phased out by 2024 as Boris Johnson says UK has duty to fight climate change as first industrialised nation|newspaper=Telegraph|language=en|date=2020-02-04|access-date=2020-02-05|last1=Yorke|first1=Harry}}</ref><ref name=BBC_51366123>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/science-environment-51366123|title=Petrol and diesel car sales ban brought forward to 2035|website=BBC News|language=en|date=2020-02-04|access-date=2020-02-05}}</ref> He also reaffirms the UK's commitment to reaching net zero carbon by 2050.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.gov.uk/government/news/pm-launches-un-climate-summit-in-the-uk|title=PM launches UN Climate Summit in the UK|website=GOV.UK|language=en|access-date=2020-02-05}}</ref>\n*6 February \u2013 [[COVID-19 in the UK]]: A third case of coronavirus is confirmed in the UK.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-51398039|title=Coronavirus: Third case confirmed in the UK\n|website=BBC News|language=en|date=2020-02-06|access-date=2020-02-06}}</ref>\n*7 February \u2013 [[Buckingham Palace]] announces that the wedding of [[Princess Beatrice of York]] and [[Edoardo Mapelli Mozzi]] will take place on 29 May.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-51415860 |title=Princess Beatrice: Royal wedding to be held on 29 May |work=BBC News |publisher=BBC |date=7 February 2020 |accessdate=7 February 2020}}</ref>\n*8\u20139 February \u2013 [[Storm Ciara]] hits the United Kingdom, bringing winds of up to {{convert|80|mph|abbr=on}}.\n*9 February \u2013 A British Airways [[Boeing 747]] aircraft makes the fastest ever subsonic New York JFK to London Heathrow crossing, achieved in 4 hours 56 minutes. It reaches ground speeds of up to 825&nbsp;mph by riding the jet stream bringing [[Storm Ciara]] to the UK.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-england-london-51433720|title=Storm helps plane beat transatlantic flight record|work=BBC News|date=9 February 2020}}</ref>\n*10 February\n**The government confirms it has begun to study the feasibility of a [[Irish Sea Bridge|Scotland-Northern Ireland bridge]], with project cost estimates of \u00a315\u201320bn.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2020/feb/10/boris-johnson-northern-ireland-scotland-bridge-plan-being-actively-looked-into-no-10|title=Government 'actively looking into' Scotland-Northern Ireland bridge|website=The Guardian|language=en|date=2020-02-10|access-date=2020-02-11}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-politics-51443191|title=Work 'under way' into Scotland-Northern Ireland bridge feasibility|website=BBC News|language=en|date=2020-02-10|access-date=2020-02-11}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.heraldscotland.com/news/18224365.whitehall-officials-begin-scoping-work-boris-bridge-linking-scotland-n-ireland/|title=Whitehall officials begin 'scoping work' on Boris Bridge linking Scotland and Northern Ireland|website=The Herald|language=en|date=2020-02-10|access-date=2020-02-11}}</ref>\n**In a \"historic\" decision, councillors reject a proposed expansion of [[Bristol Airport]], by 18 votes to seven, on the grounds that it would exacerbate [[climate change]], damage the health of local people, and harm flora and fauna.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2020/feb/11/plan-to-expand-bristol-airport-rejected-after-climate-protests|title=Plan to expand Bristol airport rejected after climate protests|website=The Guardian|language=en|date=2020-02-11|access-date=2020-02-11}}</ref>\n*11 February \u2013 \n**In the wake of the Streatham stabbing, the [[Terrorist Offenders Bill 2020|Terrorist Offenders Bill]], designed to end the early release of prisoners convicted of terrorist offences, is presented to parliament.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-51453418 |title=Emergency terror law presented to Parliament |work=BBC News |publisher=BBC |date=11 February 2020 |accessdate=12 February 2020}}</ref>\n**Following a review of the project, Prime Minister Boris Johnson announces that the controversial high-speed rail link [[High Speed 2|HS2]] will be built.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/business-51461597 |title=HS2 go-ahead controversial and difficult, admits Boris Johnson |work=BBC News |publisher=BBC |date=11 February 2020 |accessdate=11 February 2020}}</ref>\n*12 February\n**The Terrorist Offenders Bill passes unopposed through the [[House of Commons (United Kingdom)|House of Commons]] to complete the first stage of the process to becoming law.<ref name=Independent-2020-02-12>{{cite news|first=Ashley |last=Cowburn |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/uk/politics/streatham-attack-terrorist-mp-jail-bill-commons-a9332496.html |title=Streatham attack: Bill stopping early release of jailed terrorists passes unopposed in Commons |publisher=Independent Print Limited |newspaper=The Independent |date=12 February 2020 |accessdate=12 February 2020}}</ref>\n**The government announces plans to extend the remit of the media regulator [[Ofcom]] to include internet and social media content in the UK.<ref>{{cite news|first=Alex |last=Hern |url=https://www.theguardian.com/media/2020/feb/12/ofcom-to-be-put-in-charge-of-regulating-internet-in-uk |title=Ofcom to be put in charge of regulating internet in UK |publisher=Guardian Media Group |newspaper=The Guardian |date=12 February 2020 |accessdate=12 February 2020}}</ref>\n*13 February\n**[[Boris Johnson]] carries out a [[2020 British cabinet reshuffle|cabinet reshuffle]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-politics-49043973 |title=Cabinet reshuffle: Who is in Boris Johnson's new cabinet? |work=BBC News |publisher=BBC |date=13 February 2020 |accessdate=13 February 2020}}</ref>\n**[[Sajid Javid]] resigns as [[Chancellor of the Exchequer]]. He is succeeded by [[Rishi Sunak]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://news.sky.com/story/whos-in-and-whos-out-in-boris-johnsons-reshuffle-11932951|title=Sajid Javid on shock resignation as chancellor: 'No self-respecting minister would accept those conditions'|publisher=Sky News|date=13 February 2020|accessdate=13 February 2020}}</ref>\n*16 February \u2013 [[Storm Dennis]]: A record high number of flood warnings are declared over England, with 600 in place by the evening.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-51519635|title=Storm Dennis: Major incidents declared in south Wales and Herefordshire|publisher=BBC News|date=16 February 2020|accessdate=16 February 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/live/2020/feb/16/storm-dennis-met-office-issues-red-warning-south-wales-floods-live-updates?page=with:block-5e4938be8f086a28115acb1a#block-5e4938be8f086a28115acb1a|title=Record number of flood warnings in place|work=The Guardian|date=16 February 2020|accessdate=16 February 2020}}</ref> Police declare major incidents in a number of regions, including south Wales, after towns and villages north of [[Cardiff]] receive more than a month's worth of rainfall in 24 hours.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/feb/16/storm-dennis-prompts-life-threatening-flood-warnings-in-south-wales|title=Storm Dennis: police declare major incident in south Wales|work=The Guardian|date=16 February 2020|accessdate=16 February 2020}}</ref>\n*17 February \u2013 [[Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy|Business and Energy Secretary]] and [[COP26]] President [[Alok Sharma]] announces \u00a31.2 billion in funding for a new [[supercomputer]] to improve weather and climate models in the UK.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/science-environment-51504002|title=Met Office forecasters set for 'billion pound' supercomputer|publisher=BBC News|date=17 February 2020|a