er 10 people are reported to have died from COVID-19, almost doubling the UK death toll from 11 to 21. The government's aim for a \"[[herd immunity]]\" approach generates controversy.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.standard.co.uk/news/health/uk-herd-immunity-coronavirus-who-margaret-harris-a4387346.html |title=UK's 'herd immunity' approach to tackling coronavirus questioned by World Health Organisation |work=Evening Standard|date=14 March 2020 |accessdate=14 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/science-environment-51892402 |title=Coronavirus: Scientists say UK virus strategy is 'risking lives' |work=BBC News |publisher=BBC News |date=14 March 2020 |accessdate=14 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://maths.qmul.ac.uk/~vnicosia/UK_scientists_statement_on_coronavirus_measures.pdf |title=Public request to take stronger measures of socialdistancing across the UK with immediate effect |work=Queen Mary University of London |publisher=Queen Mary University of London |date=14 March 2020 |accessdate=14 March 2020}}</ref>\n**[[COVID-19 in the UK]]: [[Vice President of the United States]], [[Mike Pence]], announces the US is to extend its European [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in the United States#Travel and entry restrictions|coronavirus travel ban]] to include the UK from 16 March.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-us-canada-51891662 |title=Coronavirus: US to extend travel ban to UK and Ireland |work=BBC News |publisher=BBC |date=14 March 2020 |accessdate=14 March 2020}}</ref>\n**[[COVID-19 in the UK]]: UK retailers release a joint letter asking customers not to panic buy products after some supermarkets sell out of items such as pasta, hand gel and toilet paper.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/business-51883440 |title=Coronavirus: Supermarkets ask shoppers to be 'considerate' and stop panic buying |work=BBC News |publisher=BBC |date=14 March 2020 |accessdate=15 March 2020}}</ref>\n*15 March \n**[[COVID-19 