ian Jackson (footballer, born 1933)|Brian Jackson]], 86, English footballer ([[Liverpool F.C.|Liverpool]], [[Port Vale F.C.|Port Vale]]).<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.lfchistory.net/player_profile.asp?player_id=684|title=Players \u2013 Brian Jackson|publisher=Liverpool F.C. (history)|access-date=23 February 2020}}</ref>\n**[[Godfrey O'Donnell]], 80, Northern Irish priest, president of the [[Irish Council of Churches]] (2012\u20132014).<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.irishchurches.org/news-blog/5407/rev-fr-godfrey-odonnell-icc|title=Rev Fr Godfrey O'Donnell, ICC President 2012\u20132014|website=Irish Churches|date=17 February 2020}}</ref>\n**[[John Shrapnel]], 77, actor (''[[Gladiator (2000 film)|Gladiator]]'', ''[[Troy (film)|Troy]]'', ''[[101 Dalmatians (1996 film)|101 Dalmatians]]'').<ref>{{cite news|last=Coveney|first=Michael|url=https://www.theguardian.com/stage/2020/feb/18/john-shrapnel-obituary|title=John Shrapnel obituary|work=The Guardian|date=18 February 2020|access-date=22 February 2020}}</ref>\n*15 February \u2013 [[Caroline Flack]], 40, radio and television presenter, suicide.<ref>{{cite news|title=Caroline Flack: TV presenter dies at 40|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/entertainment-arts-51517973|work=BBC News|publisher=BBC|date=15 February 2020}}</ref>\n*16 February\n**[[Pearl Carr & Teddy Johnson|Pearl Carr]], 99, singer ([[Pearl Carr & Teddy Johnson]]).<ref>{{cite news|first=Tom |last=Ryan |url=https://escxtra.com/2020/02/16/pearl-carr-passes-away/ |title=Pearl Carr passes away at the age of 98 |work=ESCXTRA |date=16 February 2020 |accessdate=17 February 2020}}</ref>\n**[[Frances Cuka]], 83, actress (''[[Scrooge (1970 film)|Scrooge]]'', ''[[The Watcher in the Woods (1980 film)|The Watcher in the Woods]]'', ''[[Snow White: A Tale of Terror]]'').<ref>{{cite news|last=Coveney|first=Michael|url=https://www.theguardian.com/stage/2020/feb/20/frances-cuka-obituary|title=Frances Cuka obituary|work=The Guardian|date=20 February 2020|access-date=22 February 20