onavirus disease 2019|COVID-19]].<ref>{{cite news|last=Booth|first=Robert|url=https://www.theguardian.com/law/2020/apr/05/retired-senior-judge-sir-john-laws-dies-after-contracting-coronavirus|title=Retired judge and Cummings' uncle Sir John Laws dies after contracting coronavirus|work=The Guardian|date=5 April 2020}}</ref>\n**[[John Lucas (philosopher)|John Lucas]], 90, philosopher.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Lucas|first1=Edward|title=Lucas, John Randolph, FBA|url=http://announcements.telegraph.co.uk/deaths/240729/lucas-john-randolph-fba|website=The Telegraph Announcements|publisher=The Telegraph|accessdate=7 April 2020|date=6 April 2020}}</ref>\n**[[Dougie Morgan]], 73, Scottish rugby union player  ([[Stewart's Melville RFC|Stewart's Melville]], [[British and Irish Lions]], [[Scotland national rugby union team|national team]]).<ref>{{cite web|title=Stewart\u2019s Melville, Scotland and Lions great Dougie Morgan passes away|url=https://www.theoffsideline.com/stewarts-melville-scotland-and-lions-great-dougie-morgan-passes-away/|website=The Offside Line|date=5 April 2020}}</ref>\n**[[Peter Walker (cricketer, born 1936)|Peter Walker]], 84, English cricketer ([[Glamorgan County Cricket Club|Glamorgan]], [[England cricket team|national team]]).<ref>{{cite news|title=Obituary: Glamorgan and England cricketer Peter Walker|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/cricket/25748988|work=BBC Sport|publisher=BBC|date=6 April 2020}}</ref>\n*6 April \u2013 [[Black the Ripper]], 32, [[grime music|grime]] MC, rapper and cannabis activist.<ref>{{cite news|title=Black the Ripper dies aged 32: Tributes flow after death of British rapper|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2020/04/07/black-ripper-dies-aged-32-tributes-flow-death-british-rapper/|work=The Telegraph|date=7 April 2020}}</ref>\n*7 April \u2013 [[Nipper Read]], 95, police officer and boxing administrator, [[Coronavirus disease 2019|COVID-19]].<ref>{{cite news |date= 7 April 2020 |title= Kray twins detective 'Nipper' Read dies aged 95 |url