013 A man is shot dead by police in South London after a [[2020 Streatham stabbing|stabbing incident]] on [[Streatham High Road]]; police treat the incident as [[Terrorism in the United Kingdom|terrorist]]-related.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-england-london-51349664 |title=Streatham attack: Man shot dead by police after stabbings in London |work=BBC News |publisher=BBC |date=2 February 2020 |accessdate=2 February 2020}}</ref>\n*4 February \u2013 In London, Prime Minister Boris Johnson, naturalist [[David Attenborough|Sir David Attenborough]], and Italian Prime Minister [[Giuseppe Conte]] launch the [[COP26|26th session of the Conference of the Parties]] (COP26), a major UN climate summit to be held in Glasgow in November 2020.<ref name=BBC_51366123/> Johnson announces, subject to consultation, that coal power could be phased out by 2024, a year earlier than previously planned and the phase-out of new petrol and diesel vehicles could be brought forward from 2040 to 2035.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/politics/2020/02/04/coal-power-phased-2024-boris-johnson-says-uk-has-duty-fight/|title=Coal power to be phased out by 2024 as Boris Johnson says UK has duty to fight climate change as first industrialised nation|newspaper=Telegraph|language=en|date=2020-02-04|access-date=2020-02-05|last1=Yorke|first1=Harry}}</ref><ref name=BBC_51366123>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/science-environment-51366123|title=Petrol and diesel car sales ban brought forward to 2035|website=BBC News|language=en|date=2020-02-04|access-date=2020-02-05}}</ref> He also reaffirms the UK's commitment to reaching net zero carbon by 2050.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.gov.uk/government/news/pm-launches-un-climate-summit-in-the-uk|title=PM launches UN Climate Summit in the UK|website=GOV.UK|language=en|access-date=2020-02-05}}</ref>\n*6 February \u2013 [[COVID-19 in the UK]]: A third case of coronavirus is confirmed in the UK.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://ww